cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.IR 

The paper discusses a meta algorithm for tackling the problem of noisy labels in deep learning, which is a common issue in computer vision and natural language processing tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves mining data from various sources, which falls under the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper also discusses the convergence properties of the proposed algorithm, which is related to the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
